Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Introduction to Matrices", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112530126241846`*^9, 
  3.811253024051443*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"19ab8252-c78a-4bd5-a9a0-\
817a3f8afb3f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why Do We Need Matrices?", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811255681318878*^9, 
  3.8112556945868497`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e885e963-e285-497f-9a1a-\
714896d71bf5"],

Cell["\<\
Matrices provide a tool to simplify many problems we encounter in quantum \
mechanics. For example, physical operations including rotation and reflection \
through a plane are easily represented using matrices. More importantly, \
matrices offer an extremely useful representation of wavefunctions and \
operators in quantum mechanics.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81125564654323*^9, 3.8112557114364247`*^9}, {
  3.8112557775785575`*^9, 3.81125584381651*^9}, {3.9361824540453625`*^9, 
  3.9361824559090137`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a29905c0-b457-4d14-a82b-\
8da781a617a9"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["What is a Matrix?", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253196147987*^9, 
  3.811253199003931*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"642f2a09-704c-427a-8cdc-\
ad02682e0127"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A matrix is typically a two-dimensional array (meaning columns and rows) of \
numbers. We write that an ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " \[Cross] ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " matrix has ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " rows and ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " columns, and ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are known as the dimensions of the matrix. Consider an exemplary 3 \
\[Cross] 3 matrix,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253202269644*^9, 3.8112532489962463`*^9}, {
   3.8112533912075696`*^9, 3.8112534239186025`*^9}, {3.811253469405123*^9, 
   3.811253657615715*^9}, 3.8112538547655163`*^9, {3.8112540826043324`*^9, 
   3.8112540888982563`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2c91911b-c9c6-41f0-8f82-\
08a9c284c470"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["A",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "13"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "23"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "31"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "32"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "33"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 
  3.8112538382526913`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cde03fa7-c38e-49ff-ab9a-\
5e03b6e25755"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The matrix elements, as they are called, at each position in the matrix are \
usually given a subscript ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["a", 
    StyleBox["nm",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c0d59539-3c2b-4619-a017-ed7b7c83e4eb"],
 " to denote their position in the matrix."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112538577468147`*^9, 
  3.811253983350723*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"47c6681f-e58c-48bc-982f-\
17097a8551b4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There are a few special class of matrices that are worth defining here. \
Square matrices (those for which ",
 StyleBox["m ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "= ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " ) will be particularly important in quantum mechanics.  The diagonal \
elements of a square matrix are those elements for which ",
 StyleBox["m ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "= ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and the off-diagonal elements are those for which ",
 StyleBox["m ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[NotEqual] ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". A diagonal matrix is one for which all off-diagonal elements are equal to \
zero. We will see that diagonal matrices are important in many areas of \
quantum chemistry."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253985878127*^9, 3.811254067441263*^9}, {
  3.8112541440914836`*^9, 3.811254158215455*^9}, {3.811254224520264*^9, 
  3.8112542795986524`*^9}, {3.811255890943218*^9, 
  3.8112559241719666`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"414c23ac-05f2-4430-8d3d-\
d44c27661227"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The sum of the diagonal elements of a square matrix gives the trace of the \
matrix. For the matrix ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " in equation (1), the trace is given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112565348134828`*^9, 3.8112566697740316`*^9}, {
  3.811262641999277*^9, 
  3.8112626457171755`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b0990b30-13c4-4d9d-b49b-\
78904aa2ffa8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"Tr", " ", 
    StyleBox["A",
     FontWeight->"Bold"]}],
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "33"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.811256676711455*^9, 
  3.8112566996396923`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7f2002c9-15b3-4207-a5b3-\
2202625a898f"],

Cell["\<\
There is also the identity or unit matrix, which is a diagonal matrix in \
which all the diagonal elements are equal to one,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811255941839924*^9, 3.8112559435592566`*^9}, {
  3.81125607819905*^9, 3.811256110520636*^9}, {3.811256184076892*^9, 
  3.811256184410472*^9}, {3.811256582056868*^9, 
  3.811256583012508*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d4c444f0-4c5c-43b2-a028-\
51d3704ac12d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["I",
    FontWeight->"Bold"], "=", 
   RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
      {"1", "0", "...", "0"},
      {"0", "1", "...", "0"},
      {"...", "...", "...", "..."},
      {"0", "0", "...", "1"}
     },
     GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
     GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
          Offset[0.7]}, 
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
         Offset[0.2], {
          Offset[0.4]}, 
         Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}],
  Function[BoxForm`e$, 
   MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811256144405373*^9, 3.811256170250916*^9}, {
  3.8112622076322327`*^9, 
  3.8112622310838933`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"df6a9c30-0bf7-4459-bbd2-\
40612307efce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The transpose of a matrix ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", denoted as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["A",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"1072ce0a-6c13-4807-9d7d-043ef02ee518"],
 ", is generated by switching the rows and columns. Using the original \
definitions of the matrix element positions of ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " as shown in equation (1), we defined ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["A",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["T",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"a359903e-5192-4eab-af38-6d3e01310c44"],
 " as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811256227610773*^9, 
  3.811256353064907*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"43c9df62-1383-41e7-8e7e-\
5c9cd3959bfa"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["A",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox["T",
    FontWeight->"Bold"]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  TagBox[
   RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
      {
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "31"]},
      {
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "32"]},
      {
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "13"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "23"], 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "33"]}
     },
     GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
     GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
          Offset[0.7]}, 
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
         Offset[0.2], {
          Offset[0.4]}, 
         Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
   Function[BoxForm`e$, 
    MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.8112563977947598`*^9, 
  3.811256432215625*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"72447f21-e26e-49a8-a869-\
5c30fcafcd2b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Notice that the column and row designations have flipped. If the transpose \
of a matrix is equal to the matrix, that is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["A",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["T",
      FontSlant->"Plain"]], 
    StyleBox["=",
     FontWeight->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["A",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"c12d1535-300f-490c-8472-e527a72705bf"],
 ", then the matrix is symmetric."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112564451908464`*^9, 
  3.8112564953911114`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d7494844-e8cb-47ba-a240-\
6a7ca929a5e5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the context of matrices, a vector is a special case of a matrix in which \
either ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " or ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is equal to one. An ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " \[Cross] 1 matrix is a column vector, and a 1 \[Cross] ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " matrix is a row vector. Below is an example of a row vector,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112543695212135`*^9, 3.811254523799974*^9}, {
  3.81125465015841*^9, 3.8112546517142663`*^9}, {3.8112546985890703`*^9, 
  3.8112547317694025`*^9}, {3.811256018697091*^9, 
  3.811256039592452*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a2ad2e5d-7c7d-45d0-a316-\
769acb6887c1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["a",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "13"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112559638442764`*^9, 3.8112559741396627`*^9}, 
   3.81132486624515*^9},ExpressionUUID->"856ee948-bfde-452e-9726-\
6be9a69f6370"],

Cell["and a column vector,", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811256050139428*^9, 
  3.8112560541261487`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"76047fde-e3ed-445c-a049-\
483f1650ecd7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["a",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "31"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.8112560586261444`*^9, 3.8112560650300612`*^9}, {3.811324868556488*^9, 
  3.8113248698372135`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"32c495dd-bc78-4916-9d12-\
bc58f2d0f25a"],

Cell["\<\
Don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t confuse this definition of a matrix vector with the \
other vector definition in position-space (something that has both magnitude \
and direction). Sometimes we want to represent a vector (magnitude and \
direction) using a matrix vector, so it can get extra-confusing.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8112560229551*^9},ExpressionUUID->"3321c63e-4d31-4271-9d00-1fd293c79265"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Working with Matrices", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811256725119587*^9, 
  3.8112567287548695`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4d9fcdba-92cb-431b-a2a7-\
9a6235ceca45"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Addition/Subtraction and Scalar Multiplication", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811256799431723*^9, 3.811256808757992*^9}, {
  3.8112569334877453`*^9, 
  3.81125693518016*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"301c0546-5442-45c1-9167-\
7d2169006402"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The operations of addition/subtraction are relatively straightforward when \
working with matrices. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s say that you want to add two \
matrices together. You can only perform this operation if they have the same \
number of rows and columns. For two matrices ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112568150721493`*^9, 3.8112568193665714`*^9}, {
  3.811256918387252*^9, 
  3.811257026720969*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6d2914bd-7ad5-428b-939a-\
1f0e72f577df"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["A",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.811257050877017*^9, 
  3.811257053063272*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1bb0d396-b20c-4e96-b5da-\
3426c73c7c40"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["B",
   FontWeight->"Bold",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["b",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["b",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["b",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["b",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.8112570397227535`*^9, 
  3.8112570661652308`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"88535da3-8750-490c-a918-\
0c511c49b7f6"],

Cell["we can define the addition or subtraction operation as", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811257071202093*^9, 
  3.811257078866746*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"810b95ca-3d3e-429c-904e-\
94d88c13896e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["B",
    FontWeight->"Bold"]}], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"]}]},
     {
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"]}]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.811257050877017*^9, 3.811257053063272*^9}, {3.8112570935251427`*^9, 
  3.811257164805143*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"933fef1d-a37b-4353-aee4-\
2aa96903d8a9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Scalar multiplication of a matrix occurs when we multiply every element of \
a matrix by some value ",
 StyleBox["c",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ","
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811257180980486*^9, 
  3.811257252942991*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b5d5177a-c897-44ec-bc25-\
88aa1a0cbfd0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["c",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["A",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]}]], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontWeight->"Plain",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["ca",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "11"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["ca",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "12"]},
     {
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["ca",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "21"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["ca",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "22"]}
    }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
  3.811257050877017*^9, 3.811257053063272*^9}, {3.8112572618395014`*^9, 
  3.8112572748674974`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"82bf558d-e60f-4c47-923e-\
752b48202c67"],

Cell["\<\
These operations are not overly complicated and involve a straightforward \
modification of each matrix element. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811257280750164*^9, 
  3.811257310853862*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4c4bb971-3555-4cb3-aea8-\
90b6c2925023"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Matrix Multiplication", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81125731786572*^9, 
  3.8112573251265087`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3964d368-ee0e-4ca7-a89e-\
cc2fe6dcfa59"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s work through an example to see how we carry out \
matrix multiplication. Say we have a two-dimensional position vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ad42b3ba-cb2e-44bb-a817-b3032971b1d6"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "specified by the coordinates ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a327caa9-8c86-4dec-aacb-40fa63994a5b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9254bafe-9375-4d90-9cff-8349b50eafd1"],
 "). We can think of this as simply a matrix column vector, "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112574166176558`*^9, 3.811257462986678*^9}, {
  3.8112574992629347`*^9, 3.811257609535882*^9}, {3.8112576485328817`*^9, 
  3.8112576489365673`*^9}, {3.811257793617591*^9, 3.81125779412451*^9}, {
  3.811257880607819*^9, 3.811257884319482*^9}, {3.8112583081583605`*^9, 
  3.8112583093220716`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ac0602eb-c2b9-4dd2-9cf2-\
ae73f3c31e21"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
    {
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"]},
    {
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["y",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"]}
   }], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811253718311788*^9, 3.8112538382526913`*^9}, {
   3.811257050877017*^9, 3.811257053063272*^9}, {3.8112576239222193`*^9, 
   3.811257640601901*^9}, {3.811257835975027*^9, 3.8112578767721214`*^9}, 
   3.811257961550218*^9, 
   3.811258314339749*^9},ExpressionUUID->"8dbecbe9-cdeb-436f-9f9e-\
2c12998a42d8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s say we want to perform a linear transformation of ",
