d48be8b5c6d4"],

Cell["\<\
If the position of any two rows or any two columns is interchanged, then the \
determinant changes sign. Again, we can look at a general example using \
evaluation in Mathematica,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811318724662241*^9, 3.811318745986378*^9}, {
  3.8113189944005146`*^9, 3.811319014948121*^9}, {3.811319102875822*^9, 
