Cell["\<\
Equation (126) simply gives the elements of the conjugate transpose of a \
matrix (remember we switch the rows and columns and take the complex \
conjugate). Thus, the operator adjoint in matrix form is simply the conjugate \
transpose (or adjoint) of the original operator matrix.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811588004124174*^9, 3.8115880142975426`*^9}, {
  3.8115880556665926`*^9, 
