Cell["\<\
which means that for an operator to be Hermitian, the operator must be equal \
to its adjoint. Thus, we see that there is a direct connection between the \
definition of a Hermitian operator and the definition of a Hermitian matrix.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811589026546914*^9, 3.8115890855951166`*^9}, {
  3.8115902943900805`*^9, 
